The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, March 15, 2004 				 Neglect slur after death
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Krishnagar, March 14: Mita Moitra, a mother of two who consumed poison, was allegedly left to die at the block hospital in Bethuadahari.																								Her brother Arup Dutta said: We reached the hospital around 11.45 last night. She was laid on a bed but no doctor attended her. Mahananda Sardar, the doctor on duty, allegedly saw her at 1.30 am. Mita died an hour later.																								She was at her parents home at Bethuadahari, about 110 km from Calcutta, yesterday morning. She was here since her husband died two years ago, said Dutta. Circle inspector A. Rashidujjaman said a probe has begun.																								Nadias chief medical officer of health Prabas Chowdhury said: Mahananda told me that the patient was admitted around 1.20 am and put on saline.Police firing																								Police tonight fired four rounds in the air to disperse a mob at Garden Reach in Calcutta that blocked road protesting their inaction. The protesters had stalled traffic on Kacchi Sarak in the afternoon as well.
